Here's a basic structure for the frontend:

plaintext
Copy code
frontend
├── public
│   ├── index.html
│   └── ...
├── src
│   ├── components
│   │   ├── Header.js
│   │   ├── Form.js
│   │   ├── ThankYouMessage.js
│   │   └── ...
│   ├── App.js
│   ├── index.js
│   └── ...
└── ...
Implement your components according to the design provided. You can use Tailwind CSS for styling and FontAwesome for icons. Utilize the provided resources like Unsplash for images.

Backend (Node.js with Express)
For the backend, set up a Node.js project with Express for creating APIs to connect with the frontend and the database.

Here's a basic structure for the backend:

plaintext
Copy code
backend
├── controllers
│   ├── formDataController.js
│   └── emailController.js
├── models
│   ├── FormData.js
│   └── ...
├── routes
│   ├── formDataRoutes.js
│   └── ...
├── app.js
├── config.js
└── ...
